RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 56. Maiden Claiming Purse 30000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 119 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000, if for $45,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPIRITED RIDE raced in the middle of the pack on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the turn, kicked clear in upper stretch and held that margin to the wire. SHEZA NASTY GIRL raced in the middle of the pack on the inside early, navigated the bend from the three path, launched a bid passing the three sixteenths path and gained ground late. BOLD BABY chased the leader on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, continued around the turn in the two path and kept on in the stretch. SOFSTER tracked the pace setters on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the turn and showed no kick. BELLA CARMELINA trailed the field up the backstretch, swung out to the three and four path coming around the turn and made no bid. DON'T TELL KELLY led the field between horses through the early going, continued to show the way while saving ground around the turn and tired in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 83. Claiming Purse 26000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD OR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $25,000 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PERFECTLY GOLDEN saved ground around the first turn, tracked the leaders on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far bend, dueled in the lane and edged clear late. ROWSIE EXPRESS raced in the three path early, dueled on the inside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the two path around the far turn and kept on to the finish. DRY HUMOR stalked the leader on the outside through the opening half mile, navigated the second turn from the three path and chased on in the stretch. PASTA SALAD RHONDA raced in the two path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, continued around the far turn still in the two path and passed tiring horses in the lane. GRAND ARROW saved ground early, raced inside in the middle of the pack up the backstretch and around the second bend and finished evenly. TITOSCHANGEDMYLUCK raced off the pace on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the three path and never threatened. FLIRTINI raced in the four path around the first turn, dueled on the outside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the two path around the far turn and faded in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 14000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MARCH 21, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 21, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race S ince June 21, 2023 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility And Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUSTINSPEIGHTOFIT dueled on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the turn and drew off in the lane, under wraps at the wire. HIDDEN WARRIOR tracked the pace setters on the inside early, saved ground around the bend and kept on to the finish, no match for the winner. TANKINATOR dueled on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the two path and was outkicked in the stretch. TOP OF THE MINT chased the leader between horses through the opening quarter, continued around the turn from the three path and weakened in the lane. TAINO raced off the pace up the backstretch, came around the bend in the three path and showed no bid. BOONDOGGLE raced off the pace between horses through the early going, saved ground around the bend and was empty in the stretch.

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Edward Seltzer, Beverly Anderson,Helen Barbazon & Joseph B

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 4 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 62. Claiming Purse 13000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since August 21, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250, if for $5,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHE SO COOL saved ground around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn, began a bid passing the quarter pole and pulled clear. HARPER'S DO saved ground early, led the field up the backstretch, continued to show the way while racing in the two path around the far bend and was caught late. DOROTHY'S THE BOSS raced off the pace between horses through the opening half mile, began a bid from the three path headed into the second turn and improved position in the lane. OJITOS BELLOS raced in the two path around the first bend, chased the leader up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the three path and was outkicked in the stretch. PURRFECT DANI raced in the middle of the pack on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued around the second turn still in the three path and faded from there. MY JO JO raced in the three path early, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, began to move up while racing in the three path around the far turn, swung wide entering the stretch and flattened out in the final furlong. LA SANTA CLARA saved ground at the back of the pack throughout and was never a factor.
